        <h2 id="verdict">Is Rankability worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For content teams with writers and a tight tools budget: yes, easily.</strong> Starter at $49/mo is the best value in the optimiser category, and the scoring methodology genuinely matches Clearscope at less than a third of the cost.</p>

        <p><strong>For agencies wanting white-label briefs: yes.</strong> Agency plan at $199/mo is roughly half of comparable white-label-capable competitors.</p>

        <p><strong>For solo founders or small businesses without writers: almost always no.</strong> The editor cannot produce articles for you. You will still pay writers, manage briefs, and ship to your CMS by hand. The combined cost lands at $2,000–$5,500/mo — and the bottleneck is never the editor, it is the entire workflow around it.</p>

